NASH MIAMI MOTORS, INC., Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America et al., Appellees. No. 21146. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Oct. 29, 1964. Rehearing Denied Nov. 25, 1964. Daniel L. Ginsberg, Miami, Fla., for appellant. Crombie J. D. Garrett, Atty., Dept, of Justice, Louis F. Oberdorfer, Asst. Atty. Gen., Lee A. Jackson, Atty., Dept, of Justice, John B. Jones, Jr., Acting Asst. Atty., Gen., Harold C. Wilkenfield, Atty., Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., William A. Meadows, U. S. Atty., Miami, Fla., for appellee.

Before JONES and GEWIN, Circuit Judges, and ESTES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The controlling question on this appeal has been decided by this Court adversely to the contentions of the appellant. Willmut Gas & Oil Company v. Fly, 5th Cir. 1963, 322 F.2d 301, cert. den. 375 U.S. 984, 84 S.Ct. 518, 11 L.Ed.2d 473. The judgment of the district court is

Affirmed.
